<item>
            <title>[MNG-4270] ArtifactHandler, LifecycleMapping from plugin dependency is not used when plugin extensions are enabled</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-4270</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-3506&quot; title=&quot;Custom ArtifactHandler not resolved for project when an additional plugin with extensions is defined in parent pom&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MNG-3506&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MNG-3506&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed the case where two plugins with extensions enabled get in one another&apos;s way, and some artifact handlers are not loaded properly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A related issue is that artifact handlers (and lifecycle mappings) brought in via plugin dependencies are not used. This is because only the plugin&apos;s own artifact is actually scanned for extension components like ArtifactHandler or LifecycleMapping.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
